    Self-contained, self-descriptive software package that is distributed via the App Store and deployed inside a Connector; provides access to data and data processing capa­bilities; the interface of a Data App is semantically described by the IDS Information Model.
    DigitalContent
    Digital content of a particular type providing hints on its usage, e.g., listening to an Audio, navigating a Structure or accessing a List by an index.
    Duty
    The class of Duties as defined in the ODRL ontology.
    DynamicAttributeToken
    A JSON Web Token (e.g., for authorization) mediated as part of the message, formerly known as the 'DAPS Token'.
    Endpoint
    Access point of data exchange, service interaction and service description.
    EvaluationFacility
    Evaluation Facilities carry out the evaluation work during a certification process and issue the corresponding Certifications.
    Frequency
    Class of all frequencies.
    GeoPoint
    A location identified by geo coordinates.
    IdsProtocolSpecification
    List of all defined Protocol Specifications, for instance IDS-CP or IDS over Multipart.
    Instant
    A defined point in time with zero duration.
    KeyType
    Cryptographic Key Type.
    Language
    The class of languages potentially being used by textual Data Assets.
    LeftOperand
    Instances of the LeftOperand class are used as the leftOperand of a Constraint.
    Location
    Class of all locations.
    LogLevel
    Instances of ids:LogLevel can be used to specify a log level.
    MediaType
    General class of media types (formerly known as MIME types). ids:CustomMediaType is used only when no ids:IANAMediaType available.
    Participant
    Stakeholder in the International Data Spaces, assuming one or more of the predefined roles; every participant is given a unique identity by the Identity Provider.
    ParticipantCatalog
    Class that aggregates Participants from a (distributable) Catalog.
    ParticipantCertification
    Process and result of certifying an interested party in order to become a certified member of the International Data Space.
    PaymentModality
    Various pricing modalities such as idsc:FREE, idsc:FIXED_PRICE and idsc:NEGOTIATION_BASIS can be used as a pre-selection to annotate the terms of the contract.
    Permission
    The class of Permissions as defined in the ODRL ontology.
    Person
    The class of persons (people)
    PIP
    Refers to the PIP that provides a specific piece of information (URI/reference to an associated PIP interface).
    Prohibition
    The class of Prohibitions as defined in the ODRL ontology.
    Proxy
    Holds Proxy information.
    PublicKey
    Public key as used in asymmetric cryptography.
    PXP
    The reference to the PXP that operates a specific action, URI or reference to an associated PXP interface.
    QueryLanguage
    Class of query languages in which query strings may be formalized.
    QueryScope
    Class of scopes that may limit the space of query results, e.g., ALL, ACTIVE_ONLY.
    QueryTarget
    Class of recipients of a query message, e.g., BROKER, APPSTORE, ANY.
    RejectionReason
    Class of reasons that might lead to issuing a Rejection message.
    Representation
    Syntactic template of a Resource.
    RepresentationInstance
    A particular instance of given representation.
    Resource
    Resource is a single digital content or a coherent set of digital contents.
    ResourceCatalog
    Class that aggregates Resources from a (distributable) Catalog.
    RouteStep
    RouteSteps hold information about a communication pipelines between apps.
    SecurityGuarantee
    Security guarantee claimed by a security profile.
    SecurityProfile
    Set of security guarantees claimed by a Connector.
    Site
    An office or other premise at which the organization is located
    TemporalEntity
    A temporal interval, instant or a relative duration.
    TextResource
    Resource (at least partially) comprising textual content.
    Token
    A token (e.g., for authorization) mediated as part of the message.
    TokenFormat
    Possible formats for (security-related) tokens.
    UsagePolicyClass
    Defined usage policy classes in the IDS.
    UserAuthentication
    Holds User authentication information.
